a:8:{s:8:"encoding";s:5:"UTF-8";s:5:"title";s:17:"Podcast Generator";s:4:"link";s:41:"http://sourceforge.net/p/podcastgen/news/";s:11:"description";s:266:"Podcast Generator is a Free web based PHP podcasting script: publish podcasts uploading audio/video files via a web form and automatically create podcast w3c-compliant feeds including iTunes specific tags. The script also features a comprehensive web administration.";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:13:"lastBuildDate";s:20:"Jun 03, 2015 4:13 AM";s:5:"items";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:"title";s:60:"On the podcast artwork for single episodes in iTunes and iOS";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://feeds.podcastgenerator.net/~r/podcastgenerator/~3/RmLva2frZ4w/";s:11:"description";s:2073:"&lt;div class="markdown_content"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since the &lt;a class="" href="https://sourceforge.net/p/podcastgen/news/2015/01/podcast-generator-24-released"&gt;introduction of episodes embedded images in Podcast Generator&lt;/a&gt;, one of the most recurring questions has been why iTunes and the iOS Podcast app don't show the artwork associated to single episodes yet keep displaying the main podcast artwork/cover art.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The short answer to this question is that, at the moment we write, &lt;strong&gt;the iOS podcast app and iTunes do NOT seem to support the &lt;em&gt;&amp;lt;itunes:image&amp;gt;&lt;/em&gt; tag (artwork) for single episodes&lt;/strong&gt;, and they keep showing the main podcast artwork (see also &lt;a class="" href="https://discussions.apple.com/thread/6304232" rel="nofollow"&gt;discussion here&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="" href="../podcastgen.sourceforge.net"&gt;Podcast Generator&lt;/a&gt; does successfully implement &lt;a class="" href="http://www.apple.com/itunes/podcasts/specs.html" rel="nofollow"&gt;all the recommendations from Apple in regards to the itunes specific podcast tags&lt;/a&gt;, including &lt;em&gt;&amp;lt;itunes:image&amp;gt;&lt;/em&gt; both at the feed and at the item level. According to the technical specs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="" href="http://www.apple.com/itunes/podcasts/specs.html#image" rel="nofollow"&gt;The &amp;lt;itunes:image&amp;gt; tag is also supported at the &amp;lt;item&amp;gt; (episode) level&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However Apple does not implement this specific recommendation neither in the iOS podcast app nor in iTunes. Currently, the artwork associated to a single episode (&amp;lt;item&amp;gt;) using the &lt;em&gt;&amp;lt;itunes:image&amp;gt;&lt;/em&gt; tag is simply ignored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking forward to see this feature fully integrated in Apple products! :)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/podcastgenerator/~4/RmLva2frZ4w" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://sourceforge.netaf720a1bba40a295977377f30ba307e1e3768754";s:7:"pubDate";s:20:"Jun 03, 2015 4:13 AM";}}s:11:"items_count";i:1;}